<br>
start haste song<br>
swap breath of harmony into main hand<br>
stop haste song<br>
click breath of harmony<br>
start slow/snare song<br>
stop slow/snare song<br>
start regen or replenishment (regen and mana)<br>
half a second before it finishes, swap lute into main hand<br>
stop regen or replenishment<br>
<br>
That's an 9 second cycle if you add up all the cast times. Actually takes around 12-15 seconds. Nothing even remotely compares to how much effort it takes to play a bard at the peak of their power. The main thing with bards is that not only do they press at least as many buttons as any other class, they are the only class that needs to time things as carefully.<br>
<br>
In terms of grouping (*NOT* soloing) magicians and wizards are both pretty easy classes to play. A half assed magician or wizard is almost as good as a good magician or wizard. Sure, it's great if the magician can have his pet tank mez, and doesn't have to be told to DS the tank, or if the wizard bothers to root park adds and so on, but in most groups those aren't really necessary. Just knowing to burn harder on harder fights and get mana back during the easy fights, and choosing the right pet for the area are enough to be a decent magician in a group.<br>
<br>
Hardest class to play in a group? Usually whoever's pulling. Too bad that's monks only now. I used to like harmony pulling with my ranger. When I play my magician in a group, i'm usually just sitting there hitting a couple of hot keys a fight. On my ranger, i'll need to be paying attention to make sure there's no adds on the casters, snare stuff late enough to avoid agro, and so on. I play my magician when I don't want to have to pay too much attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=397.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=397.topic&start=41&stop=55>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=397.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=397.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=397.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=397.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=397.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="to